enslaver.notes: I think LAd'A was too young to have been master of 14760. Beyond 2473, Independencia 2976 carried a letter from Luis de Franca (Bahia, 1827.Feb.19) to LAdA (Malembo) reporting arrival of "Maria Gloria" with slaves. Amélia, 3071, 1837, LAdA said to be the loader of the slaves at Lagos. Deixa Falar, 3073, 1837, LAdA reported to be owner of ship's cargo and manager of its trade at Lagos. All BPPST, Class A: 1828, No. 56, SL, Ap 25, 1827, 59 and FO 315/64/46; 1837-38, No. 48, SL, Sept. 11, 1837, plus encl., 69-70; 1839, No. 22, SL, Jan. 12, 1838, plus encl., 12-13. I'm ashamed to say I haven't double checked these page refs.
